{"expireTime":9007200894403823000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-76e12d14cda4839d574d96ed5ef51de5-gatsby-remark-autolink-headersgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-prismjs-","val":"<p>Variable Fonts is a technology that can perform dynamic variations over individual characters in a font. These variations are created using vectors that describe the direction and strength of the variation. As an analogy, I would mention the difference between PNG and SVG formats. Imagine having an image with black circle in two formats, namely PNG and SVG. You get the task of adding a picture to the web with the same circle and the same size, but to make the circle thinner on mobile. With PNG, you have no choice but to upload a second image with lower stroke width. Conversely, with SVG, you don't have to create a new picture and upload it (tho you can). You can dynamically change that SVG image by imagining and edit its <code class=\"language-text\">stroke-width</code>. So you create a variation of the circle in the SVG. This analogy is incomplete, but understandably explains the difference between a static and a variable font.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use-them\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-use-them\" aria-label=\"how to use them permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use them</h2>\n<p>The usage is pretty similar to that of static fonts. You'll find a variable font (e.g. <a href=\"https://fonts.google.com/?vfonly\">here</a>; you'll find more links at the end of the article), download it to the project and refer it to CSS.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token atrule\"><span class=\"token rule\">@font-face</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">font-family</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"MyVariableFont\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">src</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token url\"><span class=\"token function\">url</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string url\">\"../fonts/&lt;your-variable-font>-VF.ttf\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Then you simple refer to this font in CSS selectors.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">body</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">font-family</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"MyVariableFont\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Using CSS property <code class=\"language-text\">font-variation-settings</code>, you are already creating variations of your font. This property brings together editing of all registered and custom axis. The axis marking is written in quotation marks and its value is placed behind it. Each axis is separated by a comma. The registered axis, which are lowercase, includes the following sheet. Each axis is complemented by their equivalent in the form of a CSS property for a static font.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\"wght\" / font-weight</li>\n<li>\"wdth\" / font-stretch</li>\n<li>\"slnt\" / font-style (oblique, angle)</li>\n<li>\"ital\" / font-style (italic)</li>\n<li>\"opsz\" / font-optical-sizing</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each font may have specified custom axes written uppercase. Uppercase is not mandatory for its own axis, but it is best practice. It also means that the axis are case-sensitive.</p>\n<p>As an example, I'll give you a caption that we set the font-weight to <code class=\"language-text\">666</code> and a slight drop of 5 degrees.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">font-variation-settings</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"wght\"</span> 666<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"slnt\"</span> 5<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"benefits\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#benefits\" aria-label=\"benefits permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Benefits</h2>\n<p>In what scenarios will the variable font pay off?</p>\n<h3 id=\"optimization-it-depends\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#optimization-it-depends\" aria-label=\"optimization it depends permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Optimization (it depends)</h3>\n<p>One with the most commonly discussed benefits of variable fonts is the size of the font file. If you use one custom font with one weight, variable fonts won't benefit you as the static font is mostly smaller. If you're using multiple weights of one font, you should start thinking about the variable font by now. Another opportunity to save on size is the italic version. If you are not using italic on the web, it is pointless to have it contained in the variable font.</p>\n<h3 id=\"you-have-dark-mode\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#you-have-dark-mode\" aria-label=\"you have dark mode permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>You have dark mode</h3>\n<p>Nowadays it's popular to have a dark mode version of your site. But this may sour the legibility of the text. Black text on a white background has more contrast than white text on black. This can be remedied by a small increase in the <code class=\"language-text\">\"wght\"</code> (<code class=\"language-text\">font-weight</code>) in dark mode, which will provide the necessary contrast. This could also address the reduction in brightness on adaptive screens when the API becomes available. If the user is in direct sunlight and the display gets dark, we use variable fonts to highlight the text and vice versa.</p>\n<h3 id=\"cretive-designs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cretive-designs\" aria-label=\"cretive designs permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cretive designs</h3>\n<p>With the help of variable fonts, interesting animations can be created to attract attention.\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/7518e/vf-static.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 134.85714285714286%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/c54d4/vf-static.webp 175w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/a3432/vf-static.webp 350w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/426ac/vf-static.webp 700w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/c139f/vf-static.webp 1050w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/c2b18/vf-static.webp 1324w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/e52aa/vf-static.jpg 175w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/70ebb/vf-static.jpg 350w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/29d31/vf-static.jpg 700w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/9ecec/vf-static.jpg 1050w,\n/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/7518e/vf-static.jpg 1324w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/41b21a046037fa81a7ae7a525e17f7fd/29d31/vf-static.jpg\"\n            alt=\"A way to use variable font (resource: fontsmith.com)\"\n            title=\"A way to use variable font (resource: fontsmith.com)\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">A way to use variable font (resource: fontsmith.com)</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The designers variable fonts open up a new realm of ideas that can be applied.\n<img src=\"/src/images/607782e22cfb82820452c1bdc83c83a9/vf-animation-demo.gif\" alt=\"Animation with use of variable fonts (resource: shillingtoneducation.com)\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"fallback\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#fallback\" aria-label=\"fallback permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Fallback</h2>\n<p>As a fallback for older browsers, CSS can be used at-rule <code class=\"language-text\">@supports</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token atrule\"><span class=\"token rule\">@supports</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token property\">font-variation-settings</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"wdth\"</span> 900<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  ...<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"intriguing-resources-and-tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#intriguing-resources-and-tools\" aria-label=\"intriguing resources and tools permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intriguing resources and tools</h2>\n<h3 id=\"v-fontscom\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#v-fontscom\" aria-label=\"v fontscom permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>v-fonts.com</h3>\n<p>It offers a clear source of variable fonts where you can try individual variable fonts and use sliders to create variations of them.\n<a href=\"https://v-fonts.com/\">https://v-fonts.com/</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"axis-praxiscom\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#axis-praxiscom\" aria-label=\"axis praxiscom permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>axis-praxis.com</h3>\n<p>Another library of variable fonts that can be edited directly on the page.\n<a href=\"https://www.axis-praxis.org/\">https://www.axis-praxis.org/</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"playtypedetailcom\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#playtypedetailcom\" aria-label=\"playtypedetailcom permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>play.typedetail.com</h3>\n<p>Interactive playground for variable fonts. This tool is more for designers.\n<a href=\"http://play.typedetail.com/\">http://play.typedetail.com/</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"firefox-font-inspector\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#firefox-font-inspector\" aria-label=\"firefox font inspector permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Firefox font inspector</h3>\n<p>An excellent tool for developers and designers are DevTools for Firefox. These include a tab in the Inspector tab, 'Fonts', where you can use GUI to edit the properties of the fonts.\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/4e6ec/firefox-font-inspector.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 39.42857142857142%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/c54d4/firefox-font-inspector.webp 175w,\n/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/a3432/firefox-font-inspector.webp 350w,\n/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/426ac/firefox-font-inspector.webp 700w,\n/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/97d4f/firefox-font-inspector.webp 827w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/4edbd/firefox-font-inspector.png 175w,\n/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/13ae7/firefox-font-inspector.png 350w,\n/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/8c557/firefox-font-inspector.png 700w,\n/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/4e6ec/firefox-font-inspector.png 827w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/10716dcca9384c00ea60bee57a3e18a3/8c557/firefox-font-inspector.png\"\n            alt=\"Rozhraní Firefox DevTools pro font (zdroj: vlastní zpracování)\"\n            title=\"Rozhraní Firefox DevTools pro font (zdroj: vlastní zpracování)\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Rozhraní Firefox DevTools pro font (zdroj: vlastní zpracování)</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"docsmicrosoftcom\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#docsmicrosoftcom\" aria-label=\"docsmicrosoftcom permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>docs.microsoft.com</h3>\n<p>Detailed specification from Microsoft\n<a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/otvaroverview\">https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/otvaroverview</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"draftscsswgorg\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#draftscsswgorg\" aria-label=\"draftscsswgorg permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>drafts.csswg.org</h3>\n<p>W3C CSS Fonts Module 4 specification\n<a href=\"https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts-4/#font-rend-desc\">https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts-4/#font-rend-desc</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"summary\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#summary\" aria-label=\"summary permalink\" class=\"Blog-share before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Summary</h2>\n<p>Variable fonts are nothing new in 2020. The technology was introduced in 2016, implemented in Photoshop in 2017 and support for the web followed in 2018. Now, according to Can I Use, it's available to 90% of users (worldwide). Two years on, variable fonts still aren't where they should be. One problem is the lack of free-to-use variable fonts, as well as the fact that IE11 does not support this technology. These ailments aside, variable fonts technology comes out as a newly unlocked room full of creative ideas and ways to shift the development of web applications.</p>"}